# Brain Blips — Core Standards

This is a **Docusaurus 3.9.2** documentation site. Most changes belong in `docs/`, not application code.

## Tooling

- **Package manager:** `pnpm` only (not npm or yarn)
- **Node:** >= 20 (`nvm use 20`)
- **Do not edit:** `build/`, `.docusaurus/`, `node_modules/`

## Before finishing

```bash
pnpm build      # required for doc/link changes (onBrokenLinks: 'throw')
pnpm typecheck  # when editing src/ or TS/JS config
```

## Scope

- Minimize diffs; avoid unrelated refactors or files the user did not ask for.
- Do not add tests unless requested — no test suite exists today.
- Do not create extra markdown files (READMEs, summaries) unless asked.

## Git

- Commit and push **only when the user explicitly asks**.
- Never commit secrets (`.env*`, API keys, tokens).

## Content areas

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/optical-network-copilot/` | Primary project docs |
| `docs/ai/`, `docs/docker/`, `docs/Kubernetes/` | Supporting guides |
| `docs/meta/` | Tooling and project meta |

See `AGENTS.md` for full agent instructions.
